Good food. Deplorable service.... this is the second incident I’ve had with them and they have been extremely rude. The 1st Time the delivery man took over an hour to deliver my food. When the restaurant tried to contact him, he wouldn’t answer. This time I placed my order, gave them my delivery address and told them the delivery would be to the lobby. Normally when I order food that’s being delivered they either ask for a phone # and if they don’t ask, they usually have called ID. But for some reason whoever  took my order didn’t ask for my number nor did he write it down from the caller ID. I waited about an hour to call to check on my order. The male who picked up refuse to let me get a word in and kept telling me that the delivery man came and waited in the lobby for 10 mins (but never called me). He then took my number and hung up in my ear. Then when the delivery man got here they charged me an additional $2. Because this wasn’t his fault that he had to come back to deliver I was still gracious enough to tip him. But when I said they over charged me, he became very disrespectful also. I DONT CARE HOW GOOD YOUR FOOD IS, IT IS NOT OK TO BE DISRESPECTFUL TO PAYING CUSTOMERS!! I’m never ordering from this place again!!!

I came here on a Friday with my girlfriend to see a live performance and get a drink. What I actually got was ripped off and headache from frustration. We arrived about an hour early before the performance (scheduled for 8). We paid 20 dollars each for the cover charge just to have a bar seat, and ours was closest to the band and actually facing them. The other seats faced toward the bar and away from the band, and if you weren't early enough to snag a bar seat you were probably crammed standing behind me as they pack people in like sardines into this place. Even though my seat was probably the best spot for the view, I had other people constantly hitting me and my seat as they entered the  dining area (which was 35 dollars). The idiots haven't realized that setting up a divider right by the coat check in and bar creates a traffic jam. The layout sucks, plain and simple. All it took was 1 look at the prices to make me not want to waste money on drinks. 9 bucks for a bud light is a joke. 12 for a martini isn't absurd for a New York bar, but I saw the waitresses bringing them to other customers and It looked like a small cup loaded with ice, which I could chug down in 2 gulps. No thanks I rather buy a pizza pie. Again, It pains me to say we got a good spot because it was actually terrible. The seats make you feel like your butt is hanging off the whole time and they are awkwardly high up so you can't rest your feet

Living right here by Cucina Bene for a while, I can say that there is a lack of good single slice options in the area, in fact, there really aren't ANY good ones in a 5 minute walking radius which is surprising being that it's New York City. If you're really craving a slice and not a whole pie, I would say that this place does a good job with their plain slice, everything else, EH. They also have a pretty killer lunch deal if you want something cheap, and they're open late if you're out of options.

Just tried this place earlier today. I'm in NYC for business and it's right by Club Quarters where i'm staying.  The pizza was great. It is thin crust though, so if you're looking for a thick crust, look elsewhere.  Very reasonably priced. My bill was $9 which included 2 slices, 4 garlic knots and a Coke Zero.  The service was OK. They weren't rude or anything, but I wouldn't call  them nice either.  All in all, a good place to go for a quick bite
